article.headline: Loyola Marymount 79, Morgan St. 62
article.story: LOS ANGELES -- Anthony Ireland scored 27 points and Ashley Hamilton added 20 points to lead Loyola Marymount to a 79-62 win over Morgan State Thursday night. Chase Flint and Ayodeji Egbeyemi grabbed 10 rebounds apiece as the Lions (6-6) held a 56-33 edge on the boards. Justin Black led Morgan State (3-6) with 15 points. Anthony Hubbard added 14 points, and DeWayne Jackson and Ian Chiles scored 10 apiece for the Bears, who have yet to play a home game this season. Loyola Marymount led 43-33 at halftime, and maintained a double-digit lead throughout the second half.
